transcript.text: On Print Shop is an integrated web to print and print order management solution to simplify ordering to delivery, helping PSP's engage B to CB to B and resellers.
The objective for a video is how you can set up unique approval processes for B to B, making the sign offs simple and fast.
This is the flow chart showing various approval flow and now we'll demonstrate the same tool.
Scenario one no approvals corporate user would login to their branded portal with their username and password.

They will select the product they want to order, mention the quantity and place order, select the payment options they have and the order would be directly sent to the PSP's production environment and they would receive the automated e-mail and invoice for the order too.
Manager approval organization having single or multiple manager for approval.
Now the user would login to the specific portal.
They can personalize the product they need.
For example just sold postcard.
You can change the text and image and see the preview and even add multiple products and place the order.
For example they are having a notepad product postcard in approval pending.
The manager would have received the e-mail for the approvals and once he logs in, if you would review the order details for the approval, they will review the details they want to approve it.
Depending on single or manager they would be notified.
The same thing if you want to delete a order added a order of quantity they would be able to do so.
Someone deleting the notepad product.
So now they would only have the postcard product they want to order and approve and they would approve those orders.
So now the order would be approved and there would be comments, the things that they're deleted those feed there in the order is free.
Scenario three, rule based approval where organizations are having specific hierarchical approvals.
So now the user would log into the portal, they would order the product they want to.
They will select the same option, complete the order.
The order would be in the approval pending status.
The manager would now receive the e-mail notification for approving the order.
So they will login, they will see the notification, they will approve the order because they don't know what the next level would be approving.
So once they approve the order, they will see who the next person would be approving this order.
And now the level 2 manager would be logging into the system.
They would review the order for approvals.
They will then approve the order and then they will see the next person who would be approving their order to now this is a Level 3 manager would be approving the order.
So they log into the system, they will see the approval pending from their account, and once they approve it would be now sent to the PSP's production environment.
You also have the flexibility to create rules to auto approve orders depending on the specific user group or amount or product.
For example, right now we have selected Alfred to auto approve orders below $100.00.
So when Alfred tries to login place the order for tackles where the order amount is less than $100, automatically the order would be approved.
Scenario four external user approval.
Customer can enter e-mail address of any external approval outside our system.

So here the corporate user would login to their portal, they will personalize the product that they have with their details and then they will mention the e-mail address of the external approval, they want to approve it and place the order.
The order would be done in the pending status and an e-mail address would be received to the external approval.
This is the e-mail, they would be receiving it and they can click on the e-mail address and they don't need to have to log into the system.
This is an external approval.
So the user would be able to approve or reject the order and once they approve the order, the order would be directly be processed and sent to the PSP's production environment.
Customized approval process.

We also have flexibility to customize solutions specific to your corporate unique approval processes Where I have worked with Co-op, MDF and even punch out to know more how to help your B to B simplify ordering.
Contact on Print Shop for personalized demo and free web to print consultancy.
